FBIS4-28681 "dreas113_c_94011" FBIS-EAS-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 North Korea U.S. Exhibition of Missiles in ROK Noted U.S. Exhibition of Missiles in ROK Noted SK1206012994 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 2114 GMT 11 Jun 94 SK1206012994 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 2114 GMT 11 Jun 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to a radio report from Seoul, the headquarters of the U.S. imperialist aggressive forces occupying South Korea opened a Patriot missile unit at the Osan air base, Kyonggi Province, on 10 June and conducted a so-called operational demonstration of Patriot missiles there. The Patriot missiles opened that day belong to a unit of the Patriot missile battalion deployed in South Korea in early April. The U.S. military side has run amok with a northward invasion by saying that day that they are always ready for action.
